casebody.data:
Sead KALAKOVIC, Appellant,
v.
James DUGAN, Respondent. WD 80767 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: April 17, 2018
Motion for Rehearing and/or Transfer to Supreme Court Denied May 29, 2018
Application for Transfer to Supreme Court Denied August 21, 2018 Craig Anthony Schlapprizzi, St. Louis, MO, Attorney for Appellant. K. Christopher Jayaram and Elizabeth M. Judy, Kansas City, MO, Attorneys for Respondent. Before Division IV: Mark D. Pfeiffer, Chief Judge, Cynthia L. Martin, Judge, and James Edward Welsh, Senior Judge 1

Order

Judge Welsh retired as an active member of the court on April 1, 2018, after oral argument in this case. He has been assigned by the Chief Justice of the Missouri Supreme Court to participate in this decision as Senior Judge.

Per Curiam:

Mr. Sead Kalakovic appeals the judgment of the Circuit Court of Lafayette County, Missouri, granting Mr. James Dugan's motion to dismiss. Because a published opinion would have no precedential value, a memorandum of law has been provided to the parties. The judgment is affirmed. Rule 84.16(b).
